<script type="application/ld+json" class="kadence-faq-schema-graph kadence-faq-schema-graph--kb-faq530_bf62ca-fb">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name": "How Long Will It Take To Reduce My Pain?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type": "Answer","text": "<p>The length of time it takes to reduce your symptoms of pain will depend on several factors, such as the severity of your condition, your overall health, and your commitment to achieving your goals.</p><p>In general, most patients begin to experience some relief after their first treatment session, but the length of time it takes to achieve optimal results will vary from person to person.</p><p>Our therapists will work closely with you to create a personalized treatment action plan that addresses your specific needs and goals. Theyll monitor your progress, provide advice on pain and adjust your plan as needed to ensure the best possible outcome. </p><p>We offer a wide range of services for chronic pain management. These include physiotherapy (physical therapy), manual therapy, pelvic health physiotherapy, trigger point therapy, myofascial release, kinesiology exercise with a personal trainer and manipulative physiotherapy.</p><p>We understand that living with chronic pain can be frustrating, but we are dedicated to helping you find relief and regain your mobility as soon as possible. Start your rehabilitation journey today!</p>"}},{"@type":"Question","name": "How Soon Can I See a Therapist?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type": "Answer","text": "<p>At Trimetrics Physiotherapy, we understand the urgency of getting relief from pain and improving mobility. We strive to provide our patients with prompt and efficient service. We schedule new patient appointments as soon as possible, however, it could vary depending on the availability of our therapists, the urgency of your case, and the time of the year. We encourage patients to contact us as soon as they are ready to schedule an appointment so that we can accommodate them as soon as possible. Our team will do their best to ensure that you are seen as soon as possible and that your pain is managed as quickly as possible.</p>"}},{"@type":"Question","name": "Do You Include At-Home Exercises?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type": "Answer","text": "<p>Yes, at Trimetrics Physiotherapy, we believe that physical activity is an important component of the recovery process. Our physiotherapists will provide you with a customized home exercise plan that is tailored to your daily activities and goals. These exercises are designed to complement the treatment you receive in the clinic and help you achieve optimal results. </p><p>They will help you to strengthen the affected areas, improve your flexibility, and promote proper healing. We believe that by incorporating an at-home comprehensive exercise program, our patients are able to achieve better results, faster recovery and reduce the risk of re-injury. </p><p>Our physiotherapists have extensive experience and will provide guidance and instruction on how to perform the exercises safely with proper movement as well as progressions as needed.</p><p>Research shows that clinical results improve when patients follow through on the exercises, and for this reason, we have a number of solutions where our trained team can guide your exercise prescription one-on-one in the physiotherapy clinic. We offer individualized exercise prescriptions and an exceptional level of care.</p>"}},{"@type":"Question","name": "Does a Previous Injury Relate to My Current Pain?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type": "Answer","text": "<p>A previous injury can often be related to current pain. At Trimetrics Physiotherapy, we understand that pain is often the result of multiple factors, and a previous injury can play a significant role. Our physiotherapists will take a comprehensive approach to assessing your condition, taking into account your medical history, including previous injuries, and any other relevant factors. </p><p>They will work with you to identify the root cause of your pain and develop a personalized treatment action plan that addresses all contributing factors. This approach is effective in managing pain and preventing re-injury. Our team will also provide education and strategies to avoid recurrence of the symptoms and future injuries. <h2 class="kt-adv-heading530_a4b718-4b wp-block-kadence-advancedheading has-theme-palette-3-color has-text-color" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading530_a4b718-4b">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<p class="kt-adv-heading530_ef1dfa-51 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading has-theme-palette-5-color has-text-color" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading530_ef1dfa-51">Reach out if you can’t find what you’re looking for.</p>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-advancedbtn kb-buttons-wrap kb-btns530_ee74d5-5e modal-trigger"><a class="kb-button kt-button button kb-btn530_38440f-36 kt-btn-size-large kt-btn-width-type-fixed kb-btn-global-inherit kt-btn-has-text-true kt-btn-has-svg-false wp-block-button__link wp-block-kadence-singlebtn" href="https://trimetricsphysio.com/contact/"><span class="kt-btn-inner-text">Contact Us</span></a></div>

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column530_f0a119-2a inner-column-2"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-accordion alignnone"><div class="kt-accordion-wrap kt-accordion-id530_bf62ca-fb kt-accordion-has-29-panes kt-active-pane-1 kt-accordion-block kt-pane-header-alignment-left kt-accodion-icon-style-arrow kt-accodion-icon-side-right" style="max-width:none"><div class="kt-accordion-inner-wrap" data-allow-multiple-open="false" data-start-open="none">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-23 kt-pane530_6d2b75-de"><h3 class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title">How Long Will It Take To Reduce My Pain?</span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></h3><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p>The length of time it takes to reduce your symptoms of pain will depend on several factors, such as the severity of your condition, your overall health, and your commitment to achieving your goals.</p>



<p>In general, most patients begin to experience some relief after their first treatment session, but the length of time it takes to achieve optimal results will vary from person to person.</p>



<p>Our therapists will work closely with you to create a personalized treatment action plan that addresses your specific needs and goals. Theyll monitor your progress, provide advice on pain and adjust your plan as needed to ensure the best possible outcome. </p>



<p>We offer a wide range of services for chronic pain management. These include physiotherapy (physical therapy), manual therapy, pelvic health physiotherapy, trigger point therapy, myofascial release, kinesiology exercise with a personal trainer and manipulative physiotherapy.</p>



<p>We understand that living with chronic pain can be frustrating, but we are dedicated to helping you find relief and regain your mobility as soon as possible. Start your rehabilitation journey today!</p>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-24 kt-pane530_3f07ee-72"><h3 class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title">How Soon Can I See a Therapist?</span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></h3><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p>At Trimetrics Physiotherapy, we understand the urgency of getting relief from pain and improving mobility. We strive to provide our patients with prompt and efficient service. We schedule new patient appointments as soon as possible, however, it could vary depending on the availability of our therapists, the urgency of your case, and the time of the year. We encourage patients to contact us as soon as they are ready to schedule an appointment so that we can accommodate them as soon as possible. Our team will do their best to ensure that you are seen as soon as possible and that your pain is managed as quickly as possible.</p>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-25 kt-pane530_9d90b1-bc"><h3 class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title">Do You Include At-Home Exercises?</span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></h3><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p>Yes, at Trimetrics Physiotherapy, we believe that physical activity is an important component of the recovery process. Our physiotherapists will provide you with a customized home exercise plan that is tailored to your daily activities and goals. These exercises are designed to complement the treatment you receive in the clinic and help you achieve optimal results. </p>



<p>They will help you to strengthen the affected areas, improve your flexibility, and promote proper healing. We believe that by incorporating an at-home comprehensive exercise program, our patients are able to achieve better results, faster recovery and reduce the risk of re-injury. </p>



<p>Our physiotherapists have extensive experience and will provide guidance and instruction on how to perform the exercises safely with proper movement as well as progressions as needed.</p>



<p>Research shows that clinical results improve when patients follow through on the exercises, and for this reason, we have a number of solutions where our trained team can guide your exercise prescription one-on-one in the physiotherapy clinic. We offer individualized exercise prescriptions and an exceptional level of care.</p>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-26 kt-pane530_1f3dac-d7"><h3 class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title">Does a Previous Injury Relate to My Current Pain?</span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></h3><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p>A previous injury can often be related to current pain. At Trimetrics Physiotherapy, we understand that pain is often the result of multiple factors, and a previous injury can play a significant role. Our physiotherapists will take a comprehensive approach to assessing your condition, taking into account your medical history, including previous injuries, and any other relevant factors. </p>



<p>They will work with you to identify the root cause of your pain and develop a personalized treatment action plan that addresses all contributing factors. This approach is effective in managing pain and preventing re-injury. Our team will also provide education and strategies to avoid recurrence of the symptoms and future injuries. Remember that pain is a symptom, not a diagnosis and its important to look at the underlying causes of the pain.</p>
</div></div></div>
</div></div></div>
</div></div>

</div></div>

                    requestAnimationFrame(function (now) {
                        window.wixFirstPaint = now;
                        dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('wixFirstPaint'));

                    observer.disconnect();
                    return true;
                }
            });
        }).observe(document.body);
    }
</script>

    One House. Four pursuits.
    Run. Box. Strengthen. Stretch.

    Private Training

    Experience one-on-one or two-on-one private training with one of our Coaches.

    Private Training sessions include a consultation on your fitness goals, a physical assessment using the In-Body 270 Machine, and a fitness program designed just for you.

    filter:
    • All
    • Strength & Conditioning
    • Boxing
    • Rehab

    Niko

    Nikos introduction to fitness began in competitive martial arts, where he earned a black belt in karate, and coached sparring and weapons classes. This launched Niko's healthy active living journey. Niko jump-started his professional career by completing his applied health science degree, becoming a certified athletic therapist. Niko has earned residencies at prestigious universities, colleges, and various international sports organizations, where he gained valuable and diverse experience in training high-level athletes for success.

    He currently focuses on building his coaching attributes in strength and conditioning, mobility flow, and boxing. Niko utilizes his knowledge in prehab, rehab, and performance to help you reach your athletic potential.

    Specialities: Strength, Functional Training & Conditioning, Boxing, Rehabilitation

    Brittney

    Brittney is a certified personal trainer with over 4.5 years in the Fitness and Sports Development Industry and over 10 years in the gym. Her journey started with overcoming personal Mental Health struggles and a passion for movement, eventually leading her to explore psychology and how it connects to long-term fitness results. She specializes in weight loss, endurance, strength building, rehabilitation, and sports development, with a focus on building both a strong mind and body.       Kitsilano Schedule

      Follow Kitsilano

      Kitsilano Instructors

      The instructors at Club Pilates are here to help you through every step of your Pilates journey.
      Nadia
      General Manager / Pilates Instructor
      Alicja

      Classes For Everybody

       
      Level 1

      Foundation

      Ideal for beginners who want a safe and effective class experience to build a solid Pilates foundation. Focus on form and alignment to help you master Pilates fundamentals, so you can get the most out of your workout as you advance. This class is ideal for all fitness levels, is easily modified for those with physical limitations, and focuses on overall body awareness.

       
      Level 1.5

      Progression

      Continue to build your practice with more complex movements and use of equipment. Start exploring more precise and dynamic exercises. Class tempo is moderate and focuses on a steady class flow. Intermediate exercises and coordinated movements are introduced, along with progressions and balance and stability challenges to give you a more demanding workout.

      *Club Pilates Level 1 FOUNDATIONS experience required.

       
      Level 2

      Evolution

      An inspiring and uplifting class that will fully challenge the body and mind. This moderate to fast paced class incorporates quick transitions and will introduce you to more advanced exercises and use of the apparatus. Focused on strength, in addition to balance and stability, this class creates dynamic challenges to elevate your practice.

      *Club Pilates Level 1.5 PROGRESSION experience required.

       
      Level 2.5

      Mastery

      Our most advanced class level challenges precision and coordination and is perfect for those who have mastered form and alignment. These advanced Pilates movements are best achieved with a deep mind-body connection created from your experience in the proceeding foundational class levels.

      *Requires at least 3 months experience in Club Pilates Level 2 EVOLUTION, or prior instructor approval. Not recommended for those with physical limitations.

      Club Pilates Signature Classes

      Intro Class

      Introduce Your Body To Pilates For Free!

      At Club Pilates, we believe that Pilates is for every type of body. The Club Pilates Intro Class is the perfect way to experience Pilates and our studio! Enjoy a 30-minute, full-body session with one of our talented Instructors each of whom have completed more than 500 hours of comprehensive Pilates training. This session is a great intro to our state-of-the-art equipment, studio, workout, and our amazing staff. Find your local studio to book your complimentary Reformer session today!

      Reformer Flow

      Full-body, Reformer-based Pilates

      Experience the benefits of classical Pilates with a twist. Our signature, contemporary Reformer class strengthens and lengthens your entire body while taking your balance and coordination to the next level. Creatively flow from the Reformer to the Springboard, Chair, Mat and more, ensuring you never experience the same class twice.

      Cardio Sculpt

      Get Moving with an Energetic Cardio Workout

      This high-energy, low-impact class is perfect for the cardio junkie. The Jumpboard facilitates plyometric movement against customizable spring tension, rather than gravity, creating an aerobic workout thats gentle on the joints. Quick transitions and endless class variations take your practice to a new level with each visit. Pump up your heart rate in this fun, full-body Pilates party! Bonus: Jumping on the Reformer has been proven to increase bone density!

      *Recommended for those already familiar with basic Pilates.

      Control

      Stand Up, Sculpt & Get Toned

      Inspired by Joseph Pilates work with dancers, Control sculpts your legs and glutes as you experience a whole new way of incorporating Pilates principles while standing up at the Springboard! The Reformer, gliding discs, fitness ball, and free weights are used to keep your body guessing and getting stronger with every class. Integrating functional, standing movement into your Pilates practice increases strength, balance, stability, and control in ways that will enhance your everyday life. This class puts the fun into functional training!

      Suspend

      Defy gravity & Strengthen with Suspension Training

      A Reformer-based workout that combines Pilates with the incredibly effective TRX suspension training system. Created by a former Navy SEAL, TRX puts your Pilates body to the test. Stability challenges enhance strength, coordination, mobility, and balance. This athletic fusion class makes daily movements more efficient and precise and is an excellent choice for those who run, golf, play tennis, cycle, and more.

      Restore

      Massage & Soothe Sore Muscles

      Experience the benefits of foam rolling and self-myofascial release in this one-of-a-kind class. Restore repairs muscles and joints with a combination of Reformer movements and functionally programmed TriggerPoint therapy myofascial release. This signature class can regenerate the body, reduce muscle soreness, increase performance and reduce the risk of injury.

      *Not recommended for those affected by osteoporosis, diabetes, high blood pressure, varicose veins, or for individuals currently pregnant.

      Center + Balance

      Stretch Better with Pilates Equipment

      Re-center and balance your body with apparatus-assisted stretching. Center + Balance involves light movement and deep stretching to leave you feeling long, loose, and ready to take on whatever the day brings. A regular stretching routine helps reduce soreness and muscle fatigue, improve performance, decrease risk of injury, and increase blood flow to your muscles.

      F.I.T.

      Build Muscle and Stamina with Interval Training

      F.I.T. is the perfect mix of high-intensity, calorie-blasting cardio work and lower-intensity, Pilates-based strength training. Enjoy longer, maximized results with a blend of interval training, traditional fitness, and contemporary Pilates. This class focuses on aerobic ability and burns more calories in less time. This boot camp-style class is dynamic, fun, and fast paced.

      *Recommended for those already familiar with Pilates; not recommended for those recovering from injury.

      Teen

      Cross-Training for Young Adults

      The perfect class for teenagers, Teen aims to build healthy habits in young participants. Build self esteem, strength and coordination for a growing body in a fun, safe environment where proper movement and body alignment is learned using the Reformer, Springboard and more.

      *Available at select locations for those 14-19 inquire with studio.

      The Benefits of Pilates

      A consistent Pilates practice can offer benefits to everybody. Whether you're an experienced athlete looking to step up your training or you're simply looking to start a new fitness routine, Pilates creates a strong foundation of balance, strength, mobility and flexibility.
      Learn More

      About Kitsilano

      Club Pilates Kitsilano is a boutique Pilates studio specializing in reformer fusion classes for anyone, at any age or fitness level. One of the inaugural Club Pilates studios in Canada, Club Pilates Kitsilano offers high-quality, life-changing training at a surprisingly affordable price. Pure to Joseph Pilates original Reformer-based Contrology Method, but modernized with group practice and expanded state-of-the-art equipment, Club Pilates delivers an unparalleled fitness experience.

Intermediate exercises and coordinated movements are introduced, along with progressions and balance and stability challenges to give you a more demanding workout.

*Club Pilates Level 1 FOUNDATIONS experience required.

 
Level 2

Evolution

An inspiring and uplifting class that will fully challenge the body and mind. This moderate to fast paced class incorporates quick transitions and will introduce you to more advanced exercises and use of the apparatus. Focused on strength, in addition to balance and stability, this class creates dynamic challenges to elevate your practice.

*Club Pilates Level 1.5 PROGRESSION experience and prior instructor approval required.

 
Level 2.5

Mastery

Our most advanced class level challenges precision and coordination and is perfect for those who have mastered form and alignment. These advanced Pilates movements are best achieved with a deep mind-body connection created from your experience in the proceeding foundational class levels.

*Requires at least 3 months experience in Club Pilates Level 2 EVOLUTION and prior instructor approval. Not recommended for those with physical limitations.

Private Training at Club Pilates

Personalize Your Practice

Throughout your Private Training journey, a knowledgeable Instructor will evaluate your physical activity level, injury profile, posture and overall health to build a Pilates workout specifically tailored to your needs. Whether you're looking for a more personalized practice or looking to level up your group classes, Private Training helps you achieve your individual goals. Find out what your body needs with a Free Private Training Assessment! Contact the front desk or your favorite Instructor to get started..
Learn More

Group Class Membership Packages

4-Pack

A 4-Pack Membership is the perfect choice for those looking to supplement an existing training program or for clients who want to work out once per week to build and maintain a solid Pilates foundation.

8-Pack

The 8-Pack Membership makes Club Pilates your go-to workout and the core of a solid fitness routine. Members who attend at least two classes per week typically see great results faster than anticipated and develop a thorough understanding of core Pilates fundamentals.

Unlimited

Plan to work out three times per week or more? The Unlimited Membership is the perfect way to meet your fitness goals. With unlimited access to your favorite Club Pilates studio, you can keep your fitness commitments with ease.

Annual
You dont want to deal with monthly dues you just want to work out. Our prepaid Annual Membership is the hassle-free option for total access to your favorite Club Pilates studio without monthly payments. Commit to your Pilates program for an entire year!
Passport

Plan to work out at multiple Club Pilates studio locations across town or across the country? With unlimited access to the largest national Pilates studio network, you can keep your Pilates practice on track with ease. US studio network only.

      Classes For Everybody

       
      Level 1

      Foundation

      Ideal for beginners who want a safe and effective class experience to build a solid Pilates foundation. Focus on form and alignment to help you master Pilates fundamentals, so you can get the most out of your workout as you advance. This class is ideal for all fitness levels, is easily modified for those with physical limitations, and focuses on overall body awareness.

       
      Level 1.5

      Progression

      Continue to build your practice with more complex movements and use of equipment. Start exploring more precise and dynamic exercises. Class tempo is moderate and focuses on a steady class flow. Intermediate exercises and coordinated movements are introduced, along with progressions and balance and stability challenges to give you a more demanding workout.

      *Club Pilates Level 1 FOUNDATIONS experience required.

       
      Level 2

      Evolution

      An inspiring and uplifting class that will fully challenge the body and mind. This moderate to fast paced class incorporates quick transitions and will introduce you to more advanced exercises and use of the apparatus. Focused on strength, in addition to balance and stability, this class creates dynamic challenges to elevate your practice.

      *Club Pilates Level 1.5 PROGRESSION experience required.

       
      Level 2.5

      Mastery

      Our most advanced class level challenges precision and coordination and is perfect for those who have mastered form and alignment. These advanced Pilates movements are best achieved with a deep mind-body connection created from your experience in the proceeding foundational class levels.

      *Requires at least 3 months experience in Club Pilates Level 2 EVOLUTION, or prior instructor approval. Not recommended for those with physical limitations.

      Club Pilates Signature Classes

      Intro Class

      Introduce Your Body To Pilates For Free!

      At Club Pilates, we believe that Pilates is for every type of body. The Club Pilates Intro Class is the perfect way to experience Pilates and our studio! Enjoy a 30-minute, full-body session with one of our talented Instructors each of whom have completed more than 500 hours of comprehensive Pilates training. This session is a great intro to our state-of-the-art equipment, studio, workout, and our amazing staff. Find your local studio to book your complimentary Reformer session today!

      Reformer Flow

      Full-body, Reformer-based Pilates

      Experience the benefits of classical Pilates with a twist. Our signature, contemporary Reformer class strengthens and lengthens your entire body while taking your balance and coordination to the next level. Creatively flow from the Reformer to the Springboard, Chair, Mat and more, ensuring you never experience the same class twice.

      Cardio Sculpt

      Get Moving with an Energetic Cardio Workout

      This high-energy, low-impact class is perfect for the cardio junkie. The Jumpboard facilitates plyometric movement against customizable spring tension, rather than gravity, creating an aerobic workout thats gentle on the joints. Quick transitions and endless class variations take your practice to a new level with each visit. Pump up your heart rate in this fun, full-body Pilates party! Bonus: Jumping on the Reformer has been proven to increase bone density!

      *Recommended for those already familiar with basic Pilates.

      Control

      Stand Up, Sculpt & Get Toned

      Inspired by Joseph Pilates work with dancers, Control sculpts your legs and glutes as you experience a whole new way of incorporating Pilates principles while standing up at the Springboard! The Reformer, gliding discs, fitness ball, and free weights are used to keep your body guessing and getting stronger with every class. Integrating functional, standing movement into your Pilates practice increases strength, balance, stability, and control in ways that will enhance your everyday life. This class puts the fun into functional training!

      Suspend

      Defy gravity & Strengthen with Suspension Training

      A Reformer-based workout that combines Pilates with the incredibly effective TRX suspension training system. Created by a former Navy SEAL, TRX puts your Pilates body to the test. Stability challenges enhance strength, coordination, mobility, and balance. This athletic fusion class makes daily movements more efficient and precise and is an excellent choice for those who run, golf, play tennis, cycle, and more.

      Restore

      Massage & Soothe Sore Muscles

      Experience the benefits of foam rolling and self-myofascial release in this one-of-a-kind class. Restore repairs muscles and joints with a combination of Reformer movements and functionally programmed TriggerPoint therapy myofascial release. This signature class can regenerate the body, reduce muscle soreness, increase performance and reduce the risk of injury.

      *Not recommended for those affected by osteoporosis, diabetes, high blood pressure, varicose veins, or for individuals currently pregnant.

      Center + Balance

      Stretch Better with Pilates Equipment

      Re-center and balance your body with apparatus-assisted stretching. Center + Balance involves light movement and deep stretching to leave you feeling long, loose, and ready to take on whatever the day brings. A regular stretching routine helps reduce soreness and muscle fatigue, improve performance, decrease risk of injury, and increase blood flow to your muscles.

      F.I.T.

      Build Muscle and Stamina with Interval Training

      F.I.T. is the perfect mix of high-intensity, calorie-blasting cardio work and lower-intensity, Pilates-based strength training. Enjoy longer, maximized results with a blend of interval training, traditional fitness, and contemporary Pilates. This class focuses on aerobic ability and burns more calories in less time. This boot camp-style class is dynamic, fun, and fast paced.

      *Recommended for those already familiar with Pilates; not recommended for those recovering from injury.

      Teen

      Cross-Training for Young Adults

      The perfect class for teenagers, Teen aims to build healthy habits in young participants. Build self esteem, strength and coordination for a growing body in a fun, safe environment where proper movement and body alignment is learned using the Reformer, Springboard and more.

      *Available at select locations for those 14-19 inquire with studio.

      The Benefits of Pilates

      A consistent Pilates practice can offer benefits to everybody. Whether you're an experienced athlete looking to step up your training or you're simply looking to start a new fitness routine, Pilates creates a strong foundation of balance, strength, mobility and flexibility.
      Learn More

      About Kitsilano

      Club Pilates Kitsilano is a boutique Pilates studio specializing in reformer fusion classes for anyone, at any age or fitness level. One of the inaugural Club Pilates studios in Canada, Club Pilates Kitsilano offers high-quality, life-changing training at a surprisingly affordable price. Pure to Joseph Pilates original Reformer-based Contrology Method, but modernized with group practice and expanded state-of-the-art equipment, Club Pilates delivers an unparalleled fitness experience.

Welcome to
Club Pilates

Club Pilates Experience

We believe that Pilates is the path to a fuller, more satisfying physical existence. We believe that being in control of your body helps you to be in control of your life. And best of all, we believe that you can start anytime.

Classes

No matter your age or level of fitness, theres a Pilates class that will work for you. See the options and find your perfect workout fit.

View Classes
Instructors

Club Pilates instructors perform hundreds of hours of training to meet teacher standards so they can provide the highest quality Pilates workouts.

Learn More
Studios

Its more than just Reformers. Club Pilates studios feature a variety of apparatus, including TRX, Exo-Chair, Bosu ball, mats, rollers, and more.

Find a Studio

Xponential Fitness

Club Pilates is a part of Xponential Fitness, a leading global franchisor of health and wellness brands across a variety of verticals, including pilates, barre, cycling, dance, yoga, boxing, strength training, stretching, and metabolic health. Founded in 2017, Xponential has 3000+ global locations and was formed with the mission to make boutique health and wellness accessible to everyone.

Our Story

Born in San Diego in 2007, Club Pilates has expanded around the globe, bringing Pilates to hundreds of thousands of people. We serve up over eight million workouts each year to our dedicated membersand were just getting started.

 

Pure to Joseph Pilates original Reformer-based Contrology Method, but modernized with group practice and expanded state-of-the-art equipment, Club Pilates offers high-quality, life-changing training at a surprisingly affordable price.

 

We believe that Pilates is the path to a fuller, more satisfying physical existence. We believe that being in control of your body helps you to be in control of your life. And best of all, we believe that you can start anytime.

Contact Us

What We Believe

Do Pilates to move better.

To bend without breaking.

To grow through changes and adjust easily

in whichever direction life goes.

 

Do Pilates to feel better.

To stand tall with confidence.

To create space for mental clarity and focus.

 

Do Pilates to live better.

To shine with gratitude and empowerment.

To get more out of your days

and ultimately your life.

 

At Club Pilates, we want to share

the benefits of Pilates with everybody.

 

Because a balanced,

more fulfilling life is within reach.

Opportunities at Club Pilates

Work With Us

Pursue your passion as your profession! See what opportunities are available at your neighborhood Club Pilates studio.

Apply Now

Own A Studio

Become a franchise owner and join the largest network of Reformer-based group Pilates studios in the world.

First Class Free First Class Free

A CLASS FOR EVERYBODY.

From high-intensity to recovery and mobility, Club Pilates classes are low-impact, fun and effective.

 

Club Pilates Signature Classes

Intro Class

Introduce Your Body to Pilates for Free!

At Club Pilates, we believe that Pilates is for every type of body. The Club Pilates Intro Class is the perfect way to experience Pilates and our studio! Enjoy a 30-minute, full-body session with one of our talented Instructors each of whom have completed more than 500 hours of comprehensive Pilates training. This session is a great intro to our state-of-the-art equipment, studio, workout, and our amazing staff. Find your local studio to book your complimentary Reformer session today!

Reformer Flow

Reformer-based Pilates with a Contemporary Approach

Experience the benefits of classical Pilates with a twist. Our signature, contemporary Reformer class strengthens and lengthens your entire body while taking your balance and coordination to the next level. Creatively flow from the Reformer to the Springboard, Chair, Mat and more, ensuring you never experience the same class twice.

Cardio Sculpt

Get Moving with an Energetic Cardio Workout

This high-energy, low-impact class is perfect for the cardio junkie. The Jumpboard facilitates plyometric movement against customizable spring tension, rather than gravity, creating an aerobic workout thats gentle on the joints. Quick transitions and endless class variations take your practice to a new level with each visit. Pump up your heart rate in this fun, full-body Pilates party! Bonus: Jumping on the Reformer has been proven to increase bone density!

*Recommended for those already familiar with basic Pilates.

Center + Balance

Stretch Better with Pilates Equipment

Re-center and balance your body with apparatus-assisted stretching. Center + Balance involves light movement and deep stretching to leave you feeling long, loose, and ready to take on whatever the day brings. A regular stretching routine helps reduce soreness and muscle fatigue, improve performance, decrease risk of injury, and increase blood flow to your muscles.

Control

Stand Up & Get Toned

Inspired by Joseph Pilates work with dancers, Control sculpts your legs and glutes as you experience a whole new way of incorporating Pilates principles while standing up at the Springboard! The Reformer, gliding discs, fitness ball, and free weights are used to keep your body guessing and getting stronger with every class. Integrating functional, standing movement into your Pilates practice increases strength, balance, stability, and control in ways that will enhance your everyday life. This class puts the fun into functional training!

Restore

Massage and Soothe Sore Muscles

Experience the benefits of foam rolling and self-myofascial release in this one-of-a-kind class. Restore repairs muscles and joints with a combination of Reformer movements and functionally programmed TriggerPoint therapy myofascial release. This signature class can regenerate the body, reduce muscle soreness, increase performance and reduce the risk of injury.

*Not recommended for those affected by osteoporosis, diabetes, high blood pressure, varicose veins, or for individuals currently pregnant.

Suspend

Defy gravity & Strengthen with Suspension Training

A Reformer-based workout that combines Pilates with the incredibly effective TRX suspension training system. Created by a former Navy SEAL, TRX puts your Pilates body to the test. Stability challenges enhance strength, coordination, mobility, and balance. This athletic fusion class makes daily movements more efficient and precise and is an excellent choice for those who run, golf, play tennis, cycle, and more.

F.I.T.

Build Muscle and Stamina with Interval Training

F.I.T. is the perfect mix of high-intensity, calorie-blasting cardio work and lower-intensity, Pilates-based strength training. Enjoy longer, maximized results with a blend of interval training, traditional fitness, and contemporary Pilates. This class focuses on aerobic ability and burns more calories in less time. This boot camp-style class is dynamic, fun, and fast paced.

*Recommended for those already familiar with Pilates; not recommended for those recovering from injury.

Teen

Cross-Training for Young Athletes

The perfect class for teenagers, Teen aims to build healthy habits in young participants. Build self esteem, strength and coordination for a growing body in a fun, safe environment where proper movement and body alignment is learned using the Reformer, Springboard and more.

*Available at select locations for those 14-19 inquire with studio.

Learn About Our Levels

 
Level 1

Foundation

Ideal for beginners who want a safe and effective class experience to build a solid Pilates foundation. Focus on form and alignment to help you master Pilates fundamentals, so you can get the most out of your workout as you advance. This class is ideal for all fitness levels, is easily modified for those with physical limitations, and focuses on overall body awareness.

 
Level 1.5

Progression

Continue to build your practice with more complex movements and use of equipment. Start exploring more precise and dynamic exercises. Class tempo is moderate and focuses on a steady class flow. Intermediate exercises and coordinated movements are introduced, along with progressions and balance and stability challenges to give you a more demanding workout.

*Club Pilates Level 1 FOUNDATIONS experience required.

 
Level 2

Evolution

An inspiring and uplifting class that will fully challenge the body and mind. This moderate to fast paced class incorporates quick transitions and will introduce you to more advanced exercises and use of the apparatus. Focused on strength, in addition to balance and stability, this class creates dynamic challenges to elevate your practice.

*Club Pilates Level 1.5 PROGRESSION experience and prior instructor approval required.

 
Level 2.5

Mastery

Our most advanced class level challenges precision and coordination and is perfect for those who have mastered form and alignment. These advanced Pilates movements are best achieved with a deep mind-body connection created from your experience in the proceeding foundational class levels.

*Requires at least 3 months experience in Club Pilates Level 2 EVOLUTION and prior instructor approval. Not recommended for those with physical limitations.

Private Training at Club Pilates

Personalize Your Practice

Throughout your Private Training journey, a knowledgeable Instructor will evaluate your physical activity level, injury profile, posture and overall health to build a Pilates workout specifically tailored to your needs. Whether you're looking for a more personalized practice or looking to level up your group classes, Private Training helps you achieve your individual goals. Find out what your body needs with a Free Private Training Assessment! Contact the front desk or your favorite Instructor to get started..
Learn More

Group Class Membership Packages

4-Pack

A 4-Pack Membership is the perfect choice for those looking to supplement an existing training program or for clients who want to work out once per week to build and maintain a solid Pilates foundation.

8-Pack

The 8-Pack Membership makes Club Pilates your go-to workout and the core of a solid fitness routine. Members who attend at least two classes per week typically see great results faster than anticipated and develop a thorough understanding of core Pilates fundamentals.

Unlimited

Plan to work out three times per week or more? The Unlimited Membership is the perfect way to meet your fitness goals. With unlimited access to your favorite Club Pilates studio, you can keep your fitness commitments with ease.

Annual
You dont want to deal with monthly dues you just want to work out. Our prepaid Annual Membership is the hassle-free option for total access to your favorite Club Pilates studio without monthly payments. Commit to your Pilates program for an entire year!
Passport

Plan to work out at multiple Club Pilates studio locations across town or across the country? With unlimited access to the largest national Pilates studio network, you can keep your Pilates practice on track with ease. US studio network only.

At Vibe Lounge, we dont just trainwe transform. Our small-group and private sessions combine strength training, Pilates, and habit coaching to help you look, feel, and perform at your best.

Online Coaching

Work on-on-one with a Vibe Lounge trainer in your own gym, on your own time.

The Vibe Lounge experience at home

Step 1: Sign up.

Choose whether you want to work with Arad or Sandrine, and sign up below.

Step 2: Consultation

After signing up, you will receive a link to our consultation form.

Once you have filled it out, you will be prompted to book an initial consultation call. During this call, your trainer will review your goals and together, you will create a strategy to set you up for success. This includes your training plan, nutrition plan, daily/weekly/monthly habits, and how you will measure your progress. After the consultation, please allow up to 48 hours for your training program to be ready.

Step 3: Program Starts

The work starts. You will be going through your program as discussed with your trainer. You can contact your trainer through the Vibe Lounge app if you have any questions. They will answer your messages within 48 hours.

Step 4: Track Progress

The Online Coaching package includes 3 optional check-in calls, which we recommend you book at the end of every month. During this call, you will review your progress with your trainer, make any necessary adjustments, and ask questions.

Get Started.

  • Online Coaching with Arad

    Work on-on-one with Arad in your own gym, on your own time.

    Sign Up

  • Online Coaching with Sandrine

    Work on-on-one with Sandrine in your own gym, on your own time.

    Sign Up

online coaching faq

  • Online coaching includes:

    • an initial call with your trainer to discuss your goal and create a strategy

    • 3 check-in calls

    • a training program (up to 5 workouts per week)

    • nutrition coaching

    • access to your trainer via the Vibe Lounge app

  • $1,499 CAD + GST for 3 months of coaching.

    The 3-month period will start on the first day of your program.

<div class="section">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p>Welcome to QubeCore Sports & Rehab, a multi-disciplinary clinic in North Vancouver. Our name reflects the importance of structure and balance in maintaining good health. At QubeCore, we focus on the connection between physical, psychological, emotional, psychosocial, and nutritional factors to support your overall well-being.</p>
<p>We provide a wide range of evidence-based services to help you achieve your health goals. Whether youre recovering from an injury, managing chronic pain, or improving performance, our integrated approach ensures personalized care tailored to your needs. Additionally, we believe that success comes through a strong commitment to being active and giving back to the community.</p>
